{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb4806fac-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s238a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"238a"},"text":"§ 238a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Use of immigration station hospitals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Immigration and Naturalization Service may, by agreement of the heads of the departments concerned, permit the Public Health Service to use hospitals at immigration stations for the care of Public Health Service patients. The Surgeon General shall reimburse the Immigration and Naturalization Service for the actual cost of furnishing fuel, light, water, telephone, and similar supplies and services, which reimbursement shall be covered into the proper Immigration and Naturalization Service appropriation, or such costs may be paid from working funds established as provided by law, but no charge shall be made for the expense of physical upkeep of the hospitals. The Immigration and Naturalization Service shall reimburse the Surgeon General for the care and treatment of persons detained in hospitals of the Public Health Service at the request of the Immigration and Naturalization Service unless such persons are entitled to care and treatment under section 249(a) ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002017"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002017"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb4806fad-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 232, formerly title V, § 502, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/710"},"text":"58 Stat. 710","children":[],"tail":", renumbered title XXI, § 2102, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/24/s2/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–24, § 2(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-04-26"},"text":"Apr. 26, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/176"},"text":"97 Stat. 176","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered title XXIII, § 2302, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/660/tIII/s311/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–660, title III, § 311(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3755"},"text":"100 Stat. 3755","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered title XXV, § 2502, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/607/tII/s201/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–607, title II, § 201(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-04"},"text":"Nov. 4, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/3062"},"text":"102 Stat. 3062","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered title XXVI, § 2602, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/690/tII/s2620/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–690, title II, § 2620(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-18"},"text":"Nov. 18, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/4244"},"text":"102 Stat. 4244","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered title XXVII, § 2702, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/381/tI/s101/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–381, title I, § 101(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-08-18"},"text":"Aug. 18, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/576"},"text":"104 Stat. 576","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered title II, § 232, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/43/tXX/s2010/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–43, title XX, § 2010(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":"–(3), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/213"},"text":"107 Stat. 213","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb4806fae-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb4806faf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb4806fb0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s249"},"text":"section 249 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, which related to persons entitled to care and treatment without charge, was repealed, and subsec. (c) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s249"},"text":"section 249 of this title","children":[],"tail":" was redesignated as subsec. (a), by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tIX/s986/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title IX, § 986(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/603"},"text":"95 Stat. 603","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb4806fb1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300aaa–1"},"text":"section 300aaa–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to renumbering by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/43"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–43","children":[],"tail":", to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300cc–1"},"text":"section 300cc–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to renumbering by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/607"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–607","children":[],"tail":", to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s300aa–1"},"text":"section 300aa–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to renumbering by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/660"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–660","children":[],"tail":", and to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s220"},"text":"section 220 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to renumbering by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/24"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–24","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb4806fb2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idb4806fb3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Secretary of Health and Human Services” substituted for “Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare” pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/88/s509/b"},"text":"section 509(b) of Pub. L. 96–88","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s3508/b"},"text":"section 3508(b) of Title 20","children":[],"tail":", Education."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb4806fb4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Abolition of Immigration and Naturalization Service and Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For abolition of Immigration and Naturalization Service, transfer of functions, and treatment of related references, see note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1551"},"text":"section 1551 of Title 8","children":[],"tail":", Aliens and Nationality."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idb4806fb5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"idb4806fb6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of Public Health Service, Surgeon General of Public Health Service, and all other officers and employees of Public Health Service, and functions all agencies of or in Public Health Service transferred to Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare by Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1966, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1966","children":[],"tail":", 31 F.R. 8855, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/1610"},"text":"80 Stat. 1610","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s202"},"text":"section 202 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of all other officers of Department of Justice and functions of all agencies and employees of such Department, with a few exceptions, transferred to Attorney General, with power vested in him to authorize their performance or performance of any of his functions by any of such officers, agencies, and employees, by sections 1 and 2 of Reorg. Plan No. 2 of 1950, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3173, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1261"},"text":"64 Stat. 1261","children":[],"tail":", which were repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554/s8/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554, § 8(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/662"},"text":"80 Stat. 662","children":[],"tail":". Immigration and Naturalization Service, referred to in this section, was a bureau in Department of Justice."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
